We move to express. We dance for the applause. We create high standards with goals to sustain what we do. 
To fulfill that void we may feel; dancing with intention always out weighs everything else. 

This is dedicated to 2022 - a moment for me where I was reminded of who I am and who I continue to become. 

When A tainted heart is felt it’s time to let go. Detach from all attachments. Because sometimes what we share is pointless. 

Letting go of 2022 and everything before that. Focusing on what’s to come, the people who are walking in, the circle that elevates me. 

I’ve been hated on my entire life; I’ve never felt so much hate than I have in my late 30’s. 

I’ve been copied, bad mouthed & taken advantage of. 

I’m a giver. But I’ve been told I give too much. 
This 2023 is dedicated boldness, persistence and non stop creation. 

If you hate me now… just wait. I have so much more for you. 😝🤘🏻

This was one of the darkest times in my life. (2020) On the outside I was checking in on everyone, teaching classes with a smile but on the inside I was incredibly broken, dark, felt I failed, I had no more reason to move forward because in my mind it was all destroyed. I (at the moment) couldn’t see how anything could be fixed. 

I was crumbling. It was such a low place; no one; not even my family/ friends,  as much as they truly tried made me see the good. I just couldn’t see it. 

I wanted to document this moment with real feeling, real tears… (it was the hardest dance I ever danced) because I wanted to look back at this moment and say… wow, look what I overcame. I wanted this to be my drive to push because I needed to see it in the future and be proud I never gave up. (Because honestly I really could’ve; I was on the brink of throwing in the towel) 

We fight everyday with ourselves and when things get very uncertain or you live with a troubled reality (whatever it may be) it’s difficult to overpass. 
IT MAY SEEM it will never get better but the reality is we need time. 

This is why working on ourselves is important and crucial to where we go from the darkness of places. 

Life is tricky but the relationship you have with you is THE most important of them all. 

Don’t give up on yourself. Take a break if needed. Dance. Congratulate yourself for where you’ve come. 
Don’t give up on you. 

No matter how difficult it gets, there’s another day, another opportunity and most of all people who love you. 

Time heals. Time is on our side. Give time to yourself. To live. To rebuild and to your spirit. 

#loveyourself

We have the right people (Staff, faculty & mentors) to make a difference. 

Imagine you land that audition?
What if you finally could choreography that piece you’ve  been wanting to? 

Our power? We have the empire to manifest your dreams!

I was at my routine hair appt. And my amazing hair dresser saw
Something of concern and said “Susie I think you need to go to Dr.  your hair is breaking & coming out.” when I got home I saw a small bald spot in the back of my head which completely surprised me and immediately I felt like throwing up.  I asked friends about their opinions and was trying to research as much as I could. 

My hair continued to fall out … I went to the Doctor and I was diagnosed with 2 forms of alopecia. I had small patches of no hair and my hair was literally falling off by the second. There was hair everywhere. 
My Dr. said it’s Because of STRESS; Your body goes in shock and it affects your hair. She said… “in Some people the hair grows out and in some it never does.” 

I panicked. I’ve always been known to have sooo much hair and having this happen was definitely a moment where self esteem affected. 

I had 2 choices. Cry and feel like a victim or stand up. 
I got  hair extensions to make it fuller but I was just hiding my distressed hair underneath and felt so trapped. 

I finally went to @epyjoel and said “chop it off!” I want to start fresh! Let’s get it platinum blonde and CUT OFF ALL THAT BAD DEAD ENERGY! 

And here we are… my hair is growing healthier; thankfully and I’m consciously changing my lifestyle; choosing to work with less stress and breathe a lot more. (A work in progress) 

I made this choice to start again and  give myself a moment. It was a hard decision in a moment in my life that was thrown at me. 

Having alopecia was something I never thought I would have yet here we are. I choose not to be ashamed and to share my story. 
As I continue to live with alopecia;  I’m in the process of making my lifestyle healthier and living in my truth. 

Thank you @epyjoel for making me feel good again and for all the encouragement. 

There’s light for all of us to find. 
💗
